title: For Sale:  Damaged EOTech XPS2-0
postcontent:
I have an EOTech XPS2-0 that has suffered some water damage. The battery compartment was not completely sealed during a recent competition, and unfortunately we experienced about 5 periods of HEAVY rain. When the day was over I dried everything but never thought to open the battery compartment until the sight started flickering the next time I tried to use it. Upon opening, I found very small beads of water in the compartment, but no rust or signs of corrosion. I DID NOT disassemble the unit to look for other non-obvious signs of damage.

The reticle now flickers/flashes and eventually goes out completely. Sometimes I can get it to come back on after a few minutes and sometimes it takes longer. Called EOTech and made the mistake of vaguely mentioning that I wasn't sure if the battery compartment was screwed on tight enough during the rain. Therefore, they will not cover the repair under warranty for this serial number. I was quoted $200-$300. I'd rather use that money towards an ACOG or HHS-1 EOTech combo.

It was purchased for $500 brand new on 12/8/12 from Midway. I know nothing about electronics so I'm not sure what/if anything could be done to repair the unit. Exterior is in like new condition. This is an authentic EOTech sight, not one of the EBay/Chinese imitations.
